# Hackatime - Complete Documentation

> Hackatime is a free, open source coding time tracker built by Hack Club. It automatically tracks your coding time across 70+ editors and IDEs using existing WakaTime plugins. Privacy-first, completely free, with no premium features or paywalls. Compatible with the WakaTime ecosystem -- just point your existing WakaTime plugin at Hackatime's API endpoint.

## Key Features

- Automatic time tracking with no manual timers
- Language and project insights
- Leaderboards to compare with other Hack Club members
- Privacy-first: only metadata tracked, never actual code
- GitHub project linking for leaderboard visibility
- OAuth 2.0 API for third-party integrations
- Completely free with no paywalls

## How It Works

Hackatime works with any WakaTime plugin. Users configure their `~/.wakatime.cfg` file to point to Hackatime's API endpoint (`https://hackatime.hackclub.com/api/hackatime/v1`) instead of WakaTime's servers. All existing WakaTime editor plugins then send heartbeat data to Hackatime automatically.

